==Description==

The '''TechDraw ExtensionPosVertChainDimension''' tool aligns vertical dimensions to create a chain dimension.

[[Image:TechDraw_ExtensionPosVertChainDimensionExample.png|400px]]
{{Caption|On the right the aligned dimensions}}

==Usage==

# Select two or more vertical dimensions.
# The first dimension defines the position. This dimension will not be move.
# There are several ways to invoke the tool:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:TechDraw_ExtensionPosVertChainDimension.svg|16px]] [[TechDraw_ExtensionPosVertChainDimension|Position Vertical Chain Dimensions]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|TechDraw → Extensions: Attributes/Modifications → [[Image:TechDraw_ExtensionPosVertChainDimension.svg|16px]] Position Vertical Chain Dimensions}} option from the menu.
# The dimensions are aligned and their dimension texts are centered.

==Notes==

* The tool can also be used to center the dimension text of a single dimension.


